com.daon.identityx.rest.model.pojo

Class RestCollection<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.daon.identityx.rest.model.pojo.RestCollection<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of an entity
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRestResource
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ApplicationCollection, AuditCollection, AuthenticationRequestCollection, AuthenticatorCollection, AuthenticatorTypeCollection, FacetCollection, PolicyCollection, RegistrationChallengeCollection, RegistrationCollection, RoleCollection, SponsorshipCollection, SystemAuthenticatorTypeCollection, TenantCollection, TokenCollection, UserCollection

    public class RestCollection<T>
extends Object
implements IRestResource
    Base class used to manage lists of entities that can be accessed at a particular url of the Rest services. The url can be simple or followed by a query string specifying various options for retrieving the list like filtering, sorting, paging or expansion of sub-entities

      • getAllowedPermissions

        public String getAllowedPermissions()
        Returns:
        permissions the authenticating token used for retrieving the list has on the collection of entities, typically CREATE and/or DELETE. This means that the same token can be used to add new entities to the list or delete entities from the list.

      • setAllowedPermissions
